## Conversation
User asked to create a branch in cwsandbox-client for handling the aviato→sandbox
rename. This was blocking the scaling research experiments because the server
(aviato repo) had been rebranded but the Python SDK still used old proto paths.

## Actions
1. Created branch feat/rename-aviato-to-sandbox from latest main (eaeb6c1)
2. Generated new Python proto stubs from aviato repo: make buf-gen-python
3. Copied gateway_pb2.py, gateway_pb2_grpc.py, secrets_pb2.py, streaming_pb2.py,
   streaming_pb2_grpc.py from aviato/gen/python/coreweave/sandbox/v1beta2/
4. Removed old atc_pb2.py, atc_pb2.pyi, atc_pb2_grpc.py
5. Rewrote imports: from coreweave.sandbox.v1beta2 → from cwsandbox._proto
6. Renamed all SDK references: atc_pb2→gateway_pb2, ATCServiceStub→GatewayServiceStub,
   ATCStreamingServiceStub→GatewayStreamingServiceStub
7. Renamed public API: tower_ids→runner_ids, runway_ids→profile_ids,
   tower_group_id→runner_group_id
8. Updated CLI flags: --tower-id→--runner-id, --runway-id→--profile-id
9. Fixed all unit tests (658 pass), integration test references updated
10. Did NOT update uv.lock (it changed but was not staged)

