- Second test run failed because mock patches in test_sandbox.py still referenced
  ATCStreamingServiceStub string in patch() calls

## Dead Ends
None - straightforward mechanical rename.

## Hints for Future Agents
- The update-protos.sh script references old buf.build package names
  (coreweave-aviato-*). It needs updating for the new package names when
  buf.build publishes the v1beta2 packages.
- The .pyi type stub files for gateway_pb2 were NOT generated. The old
  atc_pb2.pyi was deleted. Type checking for proto types will be degraded.
- The streaming_pb2.pyi and secrets_pb2.pyi are stale (still reference v1beta1
  internally in their type annotations).

## Codebase Discoveries
- Proto stubs are vendored, not generated at build time
- update-protos.sh has two modes: buf.build download and local copy
- The SDK uses grpc.aio for async, not asyncio directly
- Proto files are excluded from ruff linting (pyproject.toml extend-exclude)

